import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['values'], ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average value in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['values'], ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(data['values'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Min: {data["values"].min():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['values'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {data["values"].max():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the range of values in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    unique_values = data['values'].nunique()
    value_counts = data['values'].value_counts()
    value_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Unique Values')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique values in the volcano dataset?')
    plt.axhline(y=value_counts.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
